The author's loving grandmother was an old woman who had been wrinkled for the 20 years the author had known her. People said she was once young and pretty, but the author found that hard to believe. The author's grandmother lived with the author and took care of them after their parents moved away. Every morning, she would wake the author up, dress them, and take them to the village school, which was attached to the local temple. She was a constant, calming presence in the author's life.
